citations:
    citation-agot-eddard-xiv:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Eddard XIV"
            text_from_source: "This is the will and word of Robert of House Baratheon, the First of his Name, King of the Andals and all the rest … I do hereby command Eddard of House Stark, Lord of Winterfell and Hand of the King, to serve as Lord Regent and Protector of the Realm upon my … upon my death … to rule in my … in my stead, until my son Joffrey does come of age …"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Robert Baratheon's deathbed scene. Ned writes his will naming Ned Protector of the Realm (secretly writing 'my heir' instead of 'my son Joffrey'). Robert asks Ned to spare Daenerys. Ned sends Tomard to escort his daughters and a letter to Stannis. Renly proposes a coup; Ned refuses. Ned enlists Littlefinger to bribe the City Watch. Lancel Lannister identified as Robert's squire who kept him supplied with wine."
